title: Solano College women's soccer suffers tough 7-0 loss to visiting Modesto | Sports | dailyrepublic.com
text:
FAIRFIELD — Modesto Junior College scored five first-half goals en route to a 7-0 win over host Solano Tuesday afternoon.
Modesto added two more goals in the second half. Shaylan Roy-Williams led the Pirates with three goals for a hat trick.
FAIRFIELD — Modesto Junior College scored five first-half goals en route to a 7-0 win over host Solano Tuesday afternoon.
Modesto added two more goals in the second half. Shaylan Roy-Williams led the Pirates with three goals for a hat trick.
Solano fell to 0-5-2.
Katelyn Talbot was able to get off two shots for the Falcons and Breanna Davis had one, but neither shot directed right at the goal. Hannah Brackfield made six saves as a goalkeeper and Jasmine Calderon stopped two shots.
Modesto closed out Solano's season last year with a 1-0 win in the first round of the Northern California regional playoffs.
The Falcons will head to Los Altos Friday for a 4 p.m. match against Foothill. Solano opens the Bay Valley Conference season on Tuesday with a 4 p.m. home match against Contra Costa.
